message.content: This command is used to establish a secure shell (SSH) connection with the specified server using a private key file named "UserKey.pem". The "-C" option enables compression, and the "-L 25900:localhost:5900" option forwards local port 5900 on your computer to port 25900 on the remote server. This allows you to access the VNC (Virtual Network Computing) service running on the remote server through a local connection on your machine. The user "user" is used to authenticate with the specified EC2 instance at its public IP address: ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com.
